---
description: Rails 8 conventions for the sample todo app
alwaysApply: true
---

- Prefer Turbo Streams and Hotwire patterns over custom JavaScript.
- Keep migrations reversible.
- Use strong parameters in controllers.
- Use Rails generators instead of handwritten boilerplate where possible.
- Keep business logic in models, not views.
- Use partials for reusable view components.
- Follow RESTful routing conventions.
- Keep the schema scoped to this todo app only.
- Write or update tests for behavior changes.
